# function to scrape the website and print out the requested data
def scraper(url):
    # send GET request to the given url
    res = requests.get(url)
    # check if the request was successful
    if res.status_code == 200:
        # use BeautifulSoup to parse the response
        soup = bs4.BeautifulSoup(res.text, 'html.parser')
        # find all div elements with class "s-post-summary--stats"
        divs = soup.find_all('div', {'class': 's-post-summary--stats'})
        # create an empty list to store extracted data
        data = []
        # loop through the div elements
        for div in divs:
            # extract the required data from the div and store in a dictionary
            question_title = div.find('h3').find('a').text
            tags = [tag.text for tag in div.find('ul', {'class': 'js-post-tag-list-wrapper'}).find_all('a', {'class': 'post-tag'})]
            question_excerpt = div.find('div', {'class': 's-post-summary--content-excerpt'}).text.strip()
            question_data = {'question_title': question_title, 'tags': tags, 'question_excerpt': question_excerpt}
            # append the dictionary to the list
            data.append(question_data)
        # convert the list of dictionaries to JSON format
        json_data = json.dumps(data)
        # print the extracted data 
        print(json_data)
    else:
        # if the request was not successful, print error message
        print('There was an error with the request.')

if __name__ == '__main__':
    url = 'https://math.stackexchange.com/questions'
    scraper(url)
